    "content_hash": "3a266aa137f716f3",
    "department": "Product",
    "description": "About us\n\nWe are champions of rail, inspired to build a greener, more sustainable https://www.thetrainline.com/terms/sustainability-faqs future of travel. Trainline enables millions of travellers to find and book the best value tickets across carriers, fares, and journey options through our highly rated mobile app, website, and B2B partner channels. \n\nGreat journeys start with Trainline 🚄 \n\nNow Europe’s number 1 downloaded rail app, with over 125 million monthly visits and £5.9 billion in annual ticket sales, we collaborate with 270+ rail and coach companies in over 40 countries. We want to create a world where travel is as simple, seamless, eco-friendly and affordable as it should be. \n\nToday, we're a FTSE 250 company driven by our incredible team of over 1,000 Trainliners from 50+ nationalities, based across London, Paris, Barcelona, Milan, Edinburgh and Madrid. With our focus on growth in the UK and Europe, now is the perfect time to join us on this high-speed journey. \n\nIntroducing Product and Supply at Trainline 👋\n\nWe’re building a seamless end-to-end travel experience—from search and booking through to journey and destination. As a fast-growing consumer business operating across Europe, we serve millions of weekly customers and are the leading rail travel app in key markets including the UK, France, Italy, and Spain!\n\nOur Supply organisation powers all customer propositions across B2C, Business Travel, B2B Distribution, and partner integrations, spanning web, app, APIs, and internal tools. This role sits within European Supply Integrations, a critical area enabling our ambition to build the world’s leading rail platform and support greener travel choices.\n\nThe team manages 20+ vendor integrations covering 250+ carriers across Europe, with a focus on key growth markets. Working across multiple engineering squads, they build and maintain integrations that power core customer journeys and support wider business functions.\n\nWe’re looking for a Product Manager to join a core supply team, owning key European inventory initiatives. This is a high-impact opportunity to solve complex problems, scale our supply platform, and collaborate closely with suppliers. If you're passionate about integrations and search functionality, this role is for you!\n\nIn this role as a Product Manager at Trainline, you will...🚄\n\n - Work closely with an engineering squad (based in Paris), building strong relationships with engineers, stakeholders, and suppliers across Europe.\n\n - Partner cross-functionally with Product, Engineering, Supply, and Commercial teams to define OKRs, prioritise outcomes, and align with company goals.\n\n - Own and evolve the roadmap across short-, medium-, and long-term horizons, informed by customer insights, strategy, and market context.\n\n - Champion the customer by using insights and data to ensure the team delivers meaningful, user-focused outcomes.\n\n - Identify opportunities, navigate ambiguity, and drive impactful, outcome-led improvements.\n\n - Set and manage squad priorities, balancing new features, platform improvements, and operational needs with clear, data-informed trade-offs.\n\n - Use data to generate insights, test hypotheses, and share learnings, while managing dependencies and enabling timely decision-making across teams.\n\n - Lead Agile practices, communicate clearly with stakeholders, and build domain and technical understanding to support effective delivery and influence.\n\nWe'd love to hear from you if you have...🔍\n\n - Proven experience in a Product Management role in a tech business\n\n - Worked in a fast-paced environment where you’ve had to think on your feet and bring people together to problem solve\n\n - Led a full-stack team or led delivery coordination across multiple teams\n\n - Evidence of customer centric thinking through insights, data and experimentation\n\n - Knowledge and experience of working with dynamic systems and APIs, both internal and external\n\n - Knowledge and experience of working with Agile frameworks, writing user stories, setting sprint goals and collaborating with teams on acceptance criteria\n\n - Analytical thinking and decision making, able to weigh up conflicting priorities and make the right decision using a balance of qual and quant data inputs\n\n - Applied AI knowledge that you can leverage as part of this scope\n\n - Experience in travel/rail industry or a marketplace would be beneficial\n\nMore information:\n\nEnjoy fantastic perks like private healthcare \u0026 dental insurance, a generous work from abroad policy, 2-for-1 share purchase plans, an EV Scheme to further reduce carbon emissions, extra festive time off, and excellent family-friendly benefits. \n\nWe prioritise career growth with clear career paths, transparent pay bands, personal learning budgets, and regular learning days. Jump on board and supercharge your career from day one! \n\nWe're operate a hybrid model to work and ask that Trainliners work from the office a minimum of 60% of their time over a 12-week period. We also have a 28-day Work from Abroad policy.\n\nOur values represent the things that matter most to us and what we live and breathe everyday, in everything we do: \n\n - 💭 Think Big - We're building the future of rail \n\n - ✔️ Own It - We focus on every customer, partner and journey \n\n - 🤝  Travel Together - We're one team \n\n - ♻️ Do Good - We make a positive impact \n\nWe know that having a diverse team makes us better and helps us succeed. And we mean all forms of diversity - gender, ethnicity, sexuality, disability, nationality and diversity of thought. That's why we're committed to creating inclusive places to work, where everyone belongs and differences are valued and celebrated.\n\nInterested in finding out more about what it's like to work at Trainline? Why not check us out on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/trainline/, Instagram https://www.instagram.com/lifeattrainline/ and Glassdoor https://www.glassdoor.co.uk/Overview/Working-at-Trainline-EI_IE249203.11,20.htm! ",
